0a%20New%20%E2%80%94%20and%20Bigger%20%E2%80%94%20Genetic%20Alphabet%0Ahttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2019%2F02%2F21%2Fscience%2Fdna-hachimoji-genetic-alphabet.html%0A%0A(via%20Instapaper)\"\\naria-label=\"Email Article\">\\nEmail\\n</a>\\n\\n\\n\\n<a class=\"menu_item tumblrShare\" id=\"shareToTumblr\" href=\"http://www.tumblr.com/share?v=3&u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2019%2F02%2F21%2Fscience%2Fdna-hachimoji-genetic-alphabet.html&t=DNA+Gets+a+New+%E2%80%94+and+Bigger+%E2%80%94+Genetic+Alphabet\" target=\"_blank\">\\nTumblr\\n</a>\\n\\n\\n<!-- Currently evernote share only works for save links so donot show it on texst page -->\\n\\n\\n\\n</div>\\n</div>\\n\\n\\n<div id=\"evernote_share_menu\" class=\"popover_menu_wrapper\">\\n<div class=\"evernote_share_menu popover_menu\">\\n<form class=\"share_to_evernote_form\" action=\"/user/share_to_evernote\" method=\"post\">\\n<input type=\\'hidden\\' name=\\'form_key\\' id=\\'form_key\\' value=\\'8fFl4vzczNmjB61pGobR\\'/>\\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"bookmark_id\" id=\"share_evernote_bookmark_id\" value=\"1165660976\"/>\\n<div class=\"small_form_line group\">\\n<label for=\"share_evernote_title\">Title:</label>\\n<input type=\"text\" class=\"text\" id=\"share_evernote_title\" name=\"title\" value=\"DNA Gets a New \\xe2\\x80\\x94 and Bigger \\xe2\\x80\\x94 Genetic Alphabet\" />\\n</div>\\n<div class=\"small_form_line group\">\\n<label for=\"share_evernote_tags\">Tags:</label>\\n<input type=\"text\" class=\"text\" id=\"share_evernote_tags\" name=\"tags\" placeholder=\"(optional, comma-separated, must already exist in Evernote)\"/>\\n</div>\\n<div class=\"small_form_line group\">\\n<label for=\"share_evernote_notebook\">Notebook:</label>\\n<input type=\"text\" class=\"text\" id=\"share_evernote_notebook\" name=\"notebook\" placeholder=\"(optional, must already exist in Evernote)\"/>\\n</div>\\n<div class=\"small_form_line group\">\\n<input type=\"submit\" id=\"share_to_evernote_submit_button\" class=\"submit\" value=\"Post to Evernote\"/>\\n<a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" class=\"cancel_box\">cancel</a>\\n</div>\\n</form>\\n</div>\\n</div>\\n</div>\\n<!-- Article Title / Metadata overlay that shows up on scroll -->\\n<aside id=\"left_context_metadata\" class=\"js_control_bar_recall left_context_metadata\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\\n<div class=\"metadata\">\\n<header>DNA Gets a New \\xe2\\x80\\x94 and Bigger \\xe2\\x80\\x94 Genetic Alphabet</header>\\n\\n<div class=\"source\">\\n<div class=\"site_name\">\\n<a class=\"original\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2019/02/21/science/dna-hachimoji-genetic-alphabet.html\">nytimes.com</a>\\n</div>\\n\\n<div class=\"site_domain\">\\n<a class=\"original\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2019/02/21/science/dna-hachimoji-genetic-alphabet.html\">NY Times</a>\\n</div>\\n\\n</div>\\n\\n\\n<time class=\"meta_read_time\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\\n1 min\\n</time>\\n\\n</div>\\n\\n</aside>\\n</section>\\n<section id=\"swap_logo_capital\" class=\"js_control_bar_recall swap_logo_capital\">\\n<aside class=\"logo_capital\"></aside>\\n</section>\\n<section id=\"recall_indicator\" class=\"recall_indicator\">\\n<a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" class=\"js_control_bar_recall\">\\n<span class=\"ipicon ipicon-ellipsis\"></span>\\n</a>\\n</section>\\n</nav>\\n\\n</div>\\n</div>\\n<div class=\"container read_content_container\">\\n<main class=\"main\" aria-label=\"Article\">\\n\\n\\n<div class=\"badge-container read-tag-container js_read_tag_container\"></div>\\n\\n<div id=\"titlebar\" class=\"titlebar\">\\n<h1>DNA Gets a New \\xe2\\x80\\x94 and Bigger \\xe2\\x80\\x94 Genetic Alphabet</h1>\\n<span class=\"origin_line\">\\n\\n<a class=\"original\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2019/02/21/science/dna-hachimoji-genetic-alphabet.html\">NY Times</a>\\n\\n&middot;\\n\\nby <span class=\"author\">Carl Zimmer</span>\\n\\n\\n\\n&middot;\\n\\n\\nFebruary 21, 2019\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n</span>\\n\\n</div>\\n<div id=\"story\"data-id=\"1165660976\" data-words=\"301\" class=\"story\">\\n<article><header><div><p>matter</p></div><p>DNA is spelled out with four letters, or bases. Researchers have now built a system with eight. It may hold clues to the potential for life elsewhere in the universe and could also expand our capacity to store digital data on Earth</p><div><div><div><a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/by/carl-zimmer\"><img src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/06/12/multimedia/author-carl-zimmer/author-carl-zimmer-thumbLarge.png\"></a></div><div><p><span>By </span></p></div></div></div><div><time>Feb. 21, 2019</time></div></header><section><div><figure><div><div><div><img src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2019/02/26/science/26SCI-ZIMMER/26SCI-ZIMMER-superJumbo.jpg\"></div></div></div><figcaption><span>Animation by Millie Georgiadis/Indiana University School of Medicine</span><span><span><span>Credit...</span><span>Millie Georgiadis/Indiana University School of Medicine</span></span></span></figcaption></figure></div><div><div><p>In 1985, the chemist Steven A. Benner sat down with some colleagues and a notebook and sketched out a way to expand the alphabet of DNA. He has been trying to make those sketches real ever since.</p><p>On Thursday, Dr. Benner and a team of scientists reported success: <a href=\"http://science.sciencemag.org/cgi/doi/10.1126/science.aat0971\">in a paper, published in Science</a>, they said they have in effect doubled the genetic alphabet. </p><p>Natural DNA is spelled out with four different letters known as bases \\xe2\\x80\\x94 A, C, G and T. Dr. Benner and his colleagues have built DNA with eight bases \\xe2\\x80\\x94 four natural, and four unnatural. They named their new system Hachimoji DNA (hachi is Japanese for eight, moji for letter).</p><p>Crafting the four new bases that don\\'t exist in nature was a chemical tour-de-force. They fit neatly into DNA\\xe2\\x80\\x99s double helix, and enzymes can read them as easily as natural bases, in order to make molecules.</p></div></div><div><div><p>\\xe2\\x80\\x9cWe can do everything here that is necessary for life,\\xe2\\x80\\x9d said Dr. Benner, now <a href=\"http://www.ffame.org/sbenner.php\">a distinguished fellow at the Foundation for Applied Molecular Evolution in Florida</a>.</p><p>Hachimoji DNA could have many applications, including a far more durable way to store digital data that could last for centuries. \\xe2\\x80\\x9cThis could be huge that way,\\xe2\\x80\\x9d said Dr. Nicholas V. Hud, a biochemist at Georgia Institute of Technology who was not involved in research.</p><div><div><div><div><div><p>Thank you for your patience while we verify access.</p><p>Already a subscriber? <a href=\"https://myaccount.nytimes.com/auth/login?response_type=cookie&amp;client_id=vi&amp;redirect_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2019%2F02%2F21%2Fscience%2Fdna-hachimoji-genetic-alphabet.html&amp;asset=opttrunc\">Log in</a>.</p><p>Want all of The Times? <a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/subscription?campaignId=89WYR&amp;redirect_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2019%2F02%2F21%2Fscience%2Fdna-hachimoji-genetic-alphabet.html\">Subscribe</a>.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></section></article>\\n</div>\\n<footer id=\"footer\" class=\"footer\">\\n<span class=\"origin_line\">\\n\\n<a class=\"original\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2019/02/21/science/dna-hachimoji-genetic-alphabet.html\">NY Times</a>\\n\\n&middot;\\n\\nby <span class=\"author\">Carl Zimmer</span>\\n\\n\\n\\n&middot;\\n\\n\\nFebruary 21, 2019\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n</span>\\n</footer>\\n<!-- ### Parser\\nInstaparser\\n-->\\n</main>\\n</div>\\n<!-- Modals -->\\n<div id=\"modal_backer\" class=\"modal_backer\"></div>\\n\\n\\n<div id=\\'speedTimeRemaining\\' class=\\'speed_time_remaining container read_content_container speed_controls_ui\\'></div>\\n<div id=\\'speedRead\\' class=\\'landing_constrained container-fluid size2mode speed_read\\' data-timeSaved=\"None\"  data-remaining=\"10\"  style=\\'display:none\\'>\\n<div id=\\'speedReadProgress\\' class=\\'progress_ba